Detection Heuristics

- Identify all `webtrigger` modules in manifest.yml.
- Check handler functions for authentication header validation (e.g., HMAC, shared secret).
- Look for timestamp/nonce validation for replay protection.
- Review event handlers for input validation before processing.

Web Trigger Security Patterns

```javascript
// INSECURE - no authentication
export async function handler(request) {
  const body = JSON.parse(request.body);
  await processData(body);  // Directly processing untrusted input
  return { statusCode: 200 };
}

// SECURE - with authentication
export async function handler(request) {
  const signature = request.headers['x-signature'];
  const timestamp = request.headers['x-timestamp'];
  
  if (!verifySignature(request.body, signature, SECRET)) {
    return { statusCode: 401, body: 'Unauthorized' };
  }
  if (isReplayAttack(timestamp)) {
    return { statusCode: 400, body: 'Request expired' };
  }
  // Process validated request
}
```

